   SAN ANTONIO, Texas -- American Century Corp. said a
federal bankruptcy court has entered an order confirming its
reorganization plan, effective Friday.
   Under the plan, substantially all of the company's assets
will be acquired by Tescorp Inc., a Houston-based maker of
oilfield products, and American Century's debenture holders
will receive Tescorp common stock, convertible preferred
stock and warrants.
