   FRANKFURT, West Germany -- Mannesmannroehren-Werke AG of
Duesseldorf, a producer of steel pipes that is 75%-owned by
Mannesmann AG and 25%-owned by Thyssen AG, said it acquired
IWKA Stahlflaschen G.m.b.H., a West German maker of steel
