   Consolidated Pretax Profit
   For Fiscal 1990 Fell 18%
</HL>
<DATE>
06/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   J.NMP
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Nippon Meat Packers Inc. of Japan, citing rising costs,
said its consolidated pretax profit for the year ended March
31 fell 18% to 25.09 billion yen ($162.3 million) from 30.67
billion yen a year earlier.
   Net income fell 23% to 8.82 billion yen, or 40.99 yen a
share, from 11.52 billion yen, or 54.43 yen a share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Sales increased 11% to 658.134 billion yen from 592.623
billion yen. Sales costs and other merchandising and
administrative costs grew at a faster pace, however, pinching
profit. Ham sausage sales rose 6.6% to 144.04 billion yen,
and processed-food sales increased 12% to 97.19 billion yen.
   Nippon Meat has said its unconsolidated pretax profit rose
2.1% to 21.52 billion yen. Net income at the parent company
rose 7% to 10.04 billion yen, and sales rose 10% to 488.06
billion yen.
   The company said it expects fiscal 1991 sales of 740
billion yen, consolidated pretax profit of 30 billion yen and
net income of 10.5 billion yen.
