   Business Brief -- Snow Brand Milk Products Co.:
   Yearly Pretax Profit Fell
   11%; Transit Costs Cited
</HL>
<DATE>
06/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   J.SBM
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Snow Brand Milk Products Co., Japan's largest
dairy-products maker, reported an 11% decline in consolidated
pretax profit for the year ended March 31 to 19.23 billion
yen ($124.3 million) from 21.534 billion yen a year earlier.
   Net income slipped 3.2% to 6.5 billion yen, or 23.10 yen a
share, from 6.72 billion yen, or 24.07 yen a share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Sales increased 5.4% to 968.89 billion yen from 918.85
billion yen.
   A spokesman attributed the slip in earnings largely to
increasing costs for domestic transportation, and said the
company also was hurt by rising prices for imported
materials, as a result of yen's decline in the fiscal fourth
quarter.
   Sales of milk, other drinks and yogurt, accounting for 26%
of sales, rose 6.2% to 274.18 billion yen. Sales of butter,
cheese and other dairy products made up 17% of total sales
and totaled 160.19 billion yen, up 4.8%.
   In the current fiscal year, Snow Brand expects sales of
1.01 trillion yen, consolidated pretax profit of 20 billion
yen and net income of 6.7 billion yen.
