<HL>
   Marketing &amp; Media:
   `Tracy' Following Is Strong
   As Film Leads the Weekend
</HL>
<DATE>
06/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   DIS OPC CRC
</CO>
<IN>
RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)
</IN>
<LP>
   LOS ANGELES -- "Dick Tracy," the closely watched summer
movie from Walt Disney Co., turned in a solid performance in
its second weekend, allaying fears that it might be a flop,
entertainment industry sources said.
   "Dick Tracy" was the top-grossing film for the weekend;
preliminary estimates put its weekend gross at $15.5 million
to $16.7 million. The No. 2 film was the estimated $14.8
million opening of Orion Pictures Corp.'s "RoboCop 2." The
No. 3 movie, Carolco Pictures Inc.'s "Total Recall," made an
estimated $8.6 million for its fourth weekend.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The estimate for "Dick Tracy" appears to be a modest
26%-31% slide from the movie's $22.5 million take on its
opening weekend. "It's a very, very good hold," said Martin
Grove, box office analyst with Baseline, an entertainment
information service. Some movies have slumped as much as 45%
in their second weekend, Mr. Grove noted.
   Moreover, the weekend pattern of a sharp 47% drop on
Friday, a smoother 5% slide on Saturday from a week earlier,
and a projected 18% drop for Sunday suggests that
word-of-mouth recommendations are holding up, said Mr. Grove.
He projects that the movie will "easily" top $100 million in
gross ticket sales at U.S. theaters.
</TEXT>
